[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T17:55:21+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Switch_Mario_LuigiBrothership_scrn_26.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">In <em>Mario &amp; Luigi: Brothership</em>, the Mario Bros. journey to a location known as <strong>Lottacoins Island</strong>, a metropolitan destination where the business of Concordia gets done. The office buildings of Lottacoins Island are home to two security locks in the form of <strong>number block puzzles</strong> you\u2019ll need to get past on Lottacoins Island.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">This <em>Mario &amp; Luigi: Brothership</em> guide shows you the <strong>Lottacoins Island gate codes</strong>. Or, for those of you who are just looking for some hints, we also walk through <strong>how to solve both number block puzzles</strong", "id": 1474734, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/guides/476044/mario-luigi-brothership-lottacoins-island-gate-codes-puzzle-solutions-number-blocks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Lottacoins Island number block puzzle solutions and codes in Mario &#038; Luigi: Brothership", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T16:48:50+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A woman rides a large Belgian Draft horse in Red Dead Redemption 2\u2019s online game mode as another player admonishes the horse.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Rockstar Games via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/grand-theft-hayseed-gameplay-clip-from-red-dead-online.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Some of my favorite moments with Rockstar\u2019s <em>Red Dead Redemption 2</em> involved striking out on the dusty plains, with nothing but <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2019/2/28/18244135/red-dead-rdr2-online-horse\">a friendly horse to carry me</a> and a package full of goods. I\u2019d listen to the gentle clip clop of my horse\u2019s hooves and simply enjoy the atmosphere. Those quiet moments are lovely, but what if there was a much more dangerous alternative? What if every time I ", "id": 1474219, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/476010/red-dead-redemption-rdr-horse-carriage-speed-mod", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Red Dead Redemption fan turns every horse into a missile with a speed mod", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T16:05:10+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Nintendo\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Mario_Luigi_Brothership_scrn_35.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/473457/mario-luigi-brothership-review-nintendo-switch\">Mario &amp; Luigi: Brothership</a></em> adds a new layer to the series\u2019 turn-based combat with <strong>Battle Plugs</strong>, special gear that gives the bros extra abilities in the game\u2019s battles when equipped.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Battle Plugs can be earned throughout the game, by crafting plugs using <strong>Lumenade</strong> gathered from Sprite Bulbs. Some Battle Plugs are given to Mario and Luigi as the story progresses. Each plug can be equipped in a <strong>Power Tap</strong> \u2014 a socket, basically \u2014&nbsp;that expan", "id": 1474220, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/guides/475537/mario-luigi-brothership-battle-plugs-all-list-combos", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All Battle Plugs in Mario &#038; Luigi: Brothership and how to get them", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T15:37:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"An image of shop tickets from Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket over some showcases.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/jlee_241107_1001_ptcgp_shoptix.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">In addition to shredding open your daily <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/453190/trading-card-game-pocket-tcg-preview\">Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket</a></em> packs and maybe doing a <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/474735/pokemon-tcg-pocket-battle-event-lapras\">Lapras battle</a>, there\u2019s one other daily you should be doing to help out your friends: liking their showcases.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Each time your showcase is liked, you\u2019ll get one shop ticket \u2014 up until you get five per day. Once you have a few shop tickets you can use them to buy a handful of very use", "id": 1473880, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/475890/tcg-pocket-shop-tickets-showcases", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket PSA: We should be \u2018liking\u2019 each other\u2019s showcases", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T15:26:10+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A piece of official artwork shows the logo for The Booze of Monkey Island\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/7Vfk1h.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">A new, unofficial entry in the Monkey Island saga is currently in development from indie studio BeanAdventureAgency. Designed as a love letter to the classic point-and-click franchise, <em><a href=\"https://bean-adventure-agency.itch.io/the-booze-of-monkey-island\">The Booze of Monkey Island</a></em> is available as a free, early-access download and nails the atmosphere and wit of the earlier adventure titles.</p>\n<img src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/FRAaSW.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,3.6543818970085,100,92.691236205983\" alt=\"A screenshot from The Booze ", "id": 1473881, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/475854/booze-of-monkey-island-adventure-game-tribute", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Brush up on your insult swordfighting skills, someone is making an unofficial Monkey Island game", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T15:12:17+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/unnamed.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/pokemon-go/38713\"><em>Pok\u00e9mon Go</em></a> is hosting a \u201cHarvest Festival\u201d event from <strong>Nov. 7-12</strong>, featuring autumn-vibes Pok\u00e9mon to usher in the (hopefully) cool weather.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The event features a double candy bonus for catching Pok\u00e9mon, an increased rate to find shiny Pumpkaboo, and Mossy Lure Modules will bring in different Pok\u00e9mon, like Alolan Exeggutor, Snorlax, Pumpkaboo, and Smoliv.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Smoliv and its evolutions will also be able to be found shiny for the first time.</p>\n<img src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/jlee_2411", "id": 1473882, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon-go-guide/475844/harvest-festival-2024-smoliv-timed-research", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_vi