src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/FallloutThumNoText.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Three musical notes have come to define Fallout: C, E-flat, and E. Together, they make up a motif so powerful that it underscored one of the <em>Fallout</em> TV show\u2019s most impactful moments.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">That\u2019s important, because when I say \u201cFallout music\u201d you\u2019re probably just as likely to imagine a jaunty tune by the Ink Spots as you are a lush orchestral theme. But the latter is the emotional underpinning of the Fallout world. It evolves to suit the narrative of each subsequent Fallout game, and it gave fans goosebumps when it finally appeared in the <em>Fallout</em> TV show. And it exists be", "id": 1473432, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/videos/475857/fallout-music-inon-zur-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The meaning behind Fallout\u2019s famous theme music", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/jarl_vetreidi_fab.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/23885496/flesh-and-blood-bright-lights\"><em>Flesh and Blood</em></a>, an intense dueling experience that competes with trading card games like <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/mtg-magic-the-gathering\"><em>Magic: The Gathering</em></a> and <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/disney-lorcana\"><em>Disney Lorcana</em></a>, is making some big moves at your local game store. Later this month New Zealand-based publisher <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/23447385/flesh-and-blood-dynasty-release-date-james-white-interview\">Legend Story Studios</a> is bringing out an all-new hero in an all-new way. Toda", "id": 1473433, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/474994/fab-jarl-vetreidi-armory-deck-spoilers-reveal-preview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Flesh and Blood\u2019s Jarl Vetrei\u0111i cards revealed for the first time", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T13:34:45+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/ss_1fdda21610fa23d0ce20b5c44fab8.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The <em>Silent Hill 2</em> remake is dense, loaded with detail and suggestions left by developer Bloober Team. Silent Hill fans have been poring over the game, looking for any clues that might shed further light on the small town\u2019s mysteries. One theory has already been confirmed, thanks to detectives who <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/474188/silent-hill-2-photo-puzzle-solution-spoilers\">examined strange photos to decode a hidden phrase</a>, but others are still coming to light.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">One fan in particular has pored over tons of environmental assets, notes left behind, and other clues to paint a vivid picture of", "id": 1472961, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/475531/silent-hill-2-fan-theory-james", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This Silent Hill 2 superfan has a theory that shows a new side to James", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T13:22:27+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"GTA Online promo art for the Strickler Hat\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Rockstar Games\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/GTA-Online-20241107-10.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>The weekly <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gta-online-guides\"><em><strong>GTA Online</strong></em></a><strong> update for November 7, 2024</strong>, is live with reward events, discounts, prizes, and a new Heist Challenge.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>GTA Online </em>weekly update guide will tell you everything happening in Los Santos this week.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"tqxGpX\"><strong>GTA Online special events</strong></h2>\n<img src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/GTA-Online-20241107-1.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=", "id": 1472962, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gta-online-guides/475759/november-7-weekly-update-events-heist-challenge", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "GTA Online update for the week of November 7", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T13:11:33+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Hoyoverse via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25507224/ZenlessZoneZero_2024_06_25_16_25_49.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/zenless-zone-zero-guides\"><em>Zenless Zone Zero</em></a> is one of Hoyoverse\u2019s gacha RPGs for mobile, PlayStation 5, and Windows PC, which means that, yes, the game has <strong>codes</strong> that you can redeem for premium currency.</p>\n\n<p>In this case, <strong><em>Zenless Zone Zero</em> codes</strong> reward Polychrome and the usual other goodies \u2014 money, EXP, and the like.</p>\n\n<p>Below we list out the currently active <em>Zenless Zone Zero </em>redemption codes as of<strong> November 2024</strong> and explain how to redeem codes.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-op", "id": 1472963, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/zenless-zone-zero-guides/24191640/zzz-codes-redeem-redemption-gift-polychrome", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Zenless Zone Zero codes for November 2024", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T13:01:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/08/I7A3074-copy.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">According to Vic Michaelis (host of <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/tv/463604/dropout-cooking-show-gastronauts-host-jordan-myrick-interview\">Dropout TV</a>\u2019s improvised comedy series <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/comedy/466916/very-important-people-season-2-trailer-dropout-vic-michaelis\">Very Important People</a></em>), the key to their character (the fictional Vic Michaelis, host of the very serious and very fictional public access TV show <em>Very Important People</em>) is giving off the vibe that \u201cthis is the most important show in the world because I am hosting it.\u201d</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">They immediately emphasized: \u201cNot me; my c", "id": 1472964, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tv/474987/dropout-very-important-people-season-2-vic-michaelis-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Dropout\u2019s Vic Michaelis on Very Important People season 2 and the meaning of life", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T12:56:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\