 new <em>Donkey Kong Country 2: Diddy\u2019s Kong Quest</em> cheat code was recently discovered almost 30 years after the platforming classic debuted on the Super Nintendo (h/t <a href=\"https://www.timeextension.com/news/2024/11/29-years-later-a-new-donkey-kong-country-2-cheat-code-has-been-discovered\">Time Extension</a>).</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The cheat involves a series of button presses \u2014 Right+Y, Left+A, Up+B, Down+X \u2014 that allows the player to exit any level at any time and return to the overworld map, even if they haven\u2019t completed the stage yet.</p>\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube\"><", "id": 1472966, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/475752/new-donkey-kong-country-2-cheat-code", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Someone found a new Donkey Kong Country 2 cheat code", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/ss_7e0f0b5e80bbeb326b96467ca8700d20bdfcc530.1920x1080.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">The runaway success of Luca Galante\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/22927447/vampire-survivors-review-roguelike-bullet-hell-steam-pc-browser-8-bit-characters-power-ups\"><em>Vampire Survivors</em></a><em> </em>has inspired many imitators: new games like <em>HoloCure \u2013 Save the Fans!</em> and <em>Halls of Torment</em>, as well as spinoffs of existing popular titles like <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24074194/deep-rock-galactic-survivor-review-impressions\"><em>Deep Rock Galactic: Survivor</em></a><em> </em>and <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24183139/league-of-legends-anima-squad-swarm-summer-event-2024", "id": 1472538, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/impressions/475331/karate-survivor-game-pc", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Karate Survivor is a fun spin on the Vampire Survivors format\u2026 once you unlock the core mechanics", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T11:25:23+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Fortnite Chapter 2 Remix Choppa\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Epic Games via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Fortnite-Remix-Choppa.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><strong>Choppas </strong>have been unvaulted for <em>Fortnite</em> Chapter 2 Remix\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/475699\">Week 2 update</a>. There are now seven helicopters you can find and pilot around the island.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">During Snoop Dogg\u2019s week at the launch of Fortnite Remix, a single Choppa would spawn. But as of the new hotfix for Week 2, helicopters are officially back. </p>\n\n<p>Our <em>Fortnite</em> guide will show you where to find all of the Choppas during Fortnite Remix Week 2.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-hea", "id": 1472008, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/fortnite-guide/475753/remix-choppa-locations-map", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where to find Choppas in Fortnite Remix\u2019s Week 2 update", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T11:25:21+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Fortnite Chapter 2 Remix Spaghetti Grotto\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Epic Games\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/fortnite-chapter-2-remix-spaghetti-grott_b949c4.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><strong>Fortnite Chapter 2 Remix</strong>\u2019s is the revival and remix of Chapter 2 maps that are part the shortened season and weekly refresh schedule.</p>\n\n<p>The month-long season started with a live event and kicked off the Remix season with The Doggfather, Snoop Dogg. This season\u2019s weekly updates will a tour through Chapter 2 with updates each Thursday unvaulting weapons and vehicles that are new, old, or remixed.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Let\u2019s talk about everything new (well, everything old that\u2019s new again) in <strong>Fortnite<em> </em>Remix\u2019s Week 2 update</strong>.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-bl", "id": 1472009, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/fortnite-guide/475699/remix-week-2-loot-pool-map-changes", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What are the new map and weapon loot pool changes in Fortnite Remix\u2019s Week 2 update?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T10:59:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: DeNA, Creatures/The Pok\u00e9mon Company\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/chrome_2024-10-29_11-15-31.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">One of Pok\u00e9mon\u2019s most well-known urban legends is that there\u2019s a rare Pok\u00e9mon \u2014 Mew \u2014 hidden under a truck in<em> Pok\u00e9mon Red</em> and <em>Pok\u00e9mon Blue</em>. Where did this come from? No one really knows. When <em>Pok\u00e9mon Red</em> and <em>Blue</em> were released, the internet wasn\u2019t ubiquitous; you couldn\u2019t even Google things yet. And yet, the rumor spread across schoolyards and, yes, online, that there was a secret Mew under a pickup truck in Vermilion City. There was no Mew, and yet, the rumor persisted. In a similar vein, <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/pokemon/comments/hc8ndf/did_you_ever_press_a_button_whi", "id": 1472010, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/475706/pokemon-tcg-pocket-urban-legends", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon has always inspired urban legends \u2014 so of course Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket would have its own", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T10:20:29+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: SteelSeries\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/arctisprowirelessPS5.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">If you want the best that SteelSeries has to offer in the PC/PlayStation headset space, but understandably don\u2019t want to pay over $300 for its Arctis Nova Pro Wireless, then you\u2019re in luck. The next best thing is the Arctis Pro Wireless, and it\u2019s <a href=\"https://howl.link/fppqbhwsvesx7\">$139.99</a> at Best Buy (was $279.99). This model isn\u2019t like most of the company\u2019s other headsets; instead of having to recharge the entire headset when its battery dies, you simply swap out its battery with an extra that comes in the box, letting the gaming continue on. Each claims to deliver around 20 hours of use, and whichever isn\u2019t in use can be recharge", "id": 1471497, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/good-deals/475705/steelseries-arctis-pro-wireless-sale-gaming-headset", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "One of SteelSeries\u2019 best wireless headsets is half off at Best Buy", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-07T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Stephanie Williams flanked by Nubia of DC Comics and a funny tweet about J